                          <p class="Para">Trust marks are well known arbiters of trust. To be successful, sustainable and trustworthy the underlying certification scheme ought to implement specific requirements including transparent criteria and procedures verifying the actual trustworthiness of the recipient by an independent certification authority. The concept of an explicit trust certification scheme is set forth in this article using the example of EuroPriSe, the European Privacy Seal for IT products and IT-based services.</p>
